Stickler Thief



Stickler the thief wants to loot money from the houses arranged in a line. 
He cannot loot two consecutive houses and aims to maximize his total loot. 
Given an array, arr[] where arr[i] represents the amount of money in
the i-th house, find the maximum amount he can loot.






class Solution {
    // Function to find the maximum money the thief can get.
    public int findMaxSum(int arr[]) {
    int n = arr.length;
        if (n == 0) return 0;
        if (n == 1) return arr[0];

        int loot_two_houses_back = 0;
        int loot_one_house_back = arr[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < n; ++i) {
            int current_loot = Math.max(arr[i] + loot_two_houses_back, loot_one_house_back);
            loot_two_houses_back = loot_one_house_back;
            loot_one_house_back = current_loot;
        }

        return loot_one_house_back;
    }
}
